Box Model:
"In a document, each element is represented as a rectangular box. In CSS, each of these rectangular boxes is described using the standard 'box model'.
Each box has four edgess: the >margin edge, >border edge, >padding edge, and >content edge." --MDN

p {

/*Content - Width and Height*/

width: 50%;
/*Border*/

border: 2px solid blue;

/*Padding*/

/*padding: 10px;*/
padding-left: 40px;

/*Margin*/
/*margin: 100px;*/
/*margin-top: 500px;*/
/*margin: 20px 40px 500px 100px;*/
/*margin: 0 auto 0 auto;*/
margin: 0 auto;
margin: 50px 20px;
}

